Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:01.959 --> 00:00:06.450
If you have an interest in art and design
and wish to combine it with the digital world

00:00:06.450 --> 00:00:09.770
then Creative Technology may well be the course
for you.

00:00:09.770 --> 00:00:16.600
And now is a great time to enter these fields
with converging technologies in the field

00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:23.560
of television, games, web, mobile and film,
what better time to enter than now.

00:00:23.560 --> 00:00:26.550
As the name creative technology suggests:

00:00:26.550 --> 00:00:32.820
C stands for Creative Industries, where our
students will enter a diverse range of subjects

00:00:32.820 --> 00:00:39.329
such as digital illustration, motion graphics
and visual effects. And where better to study

00:00:39.329 --> 00:00:46.280
these than in London the creative capital
of Europe in our purpose built labs and studios.

00:00:46.280 --> 00:00:53.100
R stands for the Range of subjects you will
be studying from visual story-telling, motion

00:00:53.100 --> 00:00:58.730
graphics for television, interactive design,
both design and scripting for new media to

00:00:58.730 --> 00:01:03.660
name a few core subjects as well as options
in 3D modelling and animation.

00:01:03.660 --> 00:01:09.920
E stands for Employment and we will help our
students stay in employment through our careers

00:01:09.920 --> 00:01:16.500
services, through our placements - after the
second year- and through professional practice

00:01:16.500 --> 00:01:22.630
modules created to build a portfolio ready
for industry.

00:01:22.630 --> 00:01:27.649
A stands for Animation and 2 or 3D animations
and stuff especially in the form of commercial

00:01:27.649 --> 00:01:32.789
graphics as you can see from the range of
work behind me.

00:01:32.789 --> 00:01:38.660
T stands for Technology and you will study
industry standard applications, in depth such

00:01:38.660 --> 00:01:43.790
as Adobe CS, which of course includes After
Effects, Photoshop, Premiere and many, many

00:01:43.790 --> 00:01:50.399
more, but also specific and specialist applications
such as Nuke and optionally Maya, which allow

00:01:50.399 --> 00:01:55.790
you to create high end visual effects and
some of our students have gone on to work

00:01:55.790 --> 00:02:01.620
as compositors for famous companies such as
FrameStore and worked on Avatar, Sherlock

00:02:01.620 --> 00:02:04.049
Holmes and Harry Potter.

00:02:04.049 --> 00:02:11.590
I stands for Interaction and in the multimedia
module, you'll study both design and code

00:02:11.590 --> 00:02:19.440
to make content interactive using Flash or
HTML5, and this offers great opportunities

00:02:19.440 --> 00:02:23.020
for our students for employment and it's very
much in demand by industry.

00:02:23.020 --> 00:02:29.600
V stands for Visual Effects especially compositing
in 2 and 3D for television and film using

00:02:29.600 --> 00:02:34.780
our specialist software as I said before.
As well as the opportunity to film original

00:02:34.780 --> 00:02:41.470
content in our green screen studios and you'll
be able to tap into the expertise of our lecturers,

00:02:41.470 --> 00:02:47.970
of our technicians and professional practitioners
who regularly us here at Kingston.

00:02:47.970 --> 00:02:54.580
E stands for Editing and you will study the
core soft skills such as when to edit, cut,

00:02:54.580 --> 00:03:02.190
fade, zoom and so on. But also harder skills
such as multi-platform renders, pixel depth,

00:03:02.190 --> 00:03:05.790
aspect ratios and conversions.

00:03:05.790 --> 00:03:10.740
T stands for Teaching and here at Kingston
we have developed a broad range of strategies

00:03:10.740 --> 00:03:16.540
from one to-one tutorial system with our students
to lectures, seminars, weekly workshops, visits

00:03:16.540 --> 00:03:22.700
and individual, group and project to develop
those vital skills for industry.

00:03:22.700 --> 00:03:29.210
E stands for E-Learning and we fully embrace
the new forms of digital learning as embodied

00:03:29.210 --> 00:03:35.890
in our StudySpace platform. Here lectures,
workshops, seminars, blogs, discussions in

00:03:35.890 --> 00:03:41.800
text, audio and interactive modes are employed
to encourage teaching and learning appropriate

00:03:41.800 --> 00:03:45.300
for the twenty first century.

00:03:45.300 --> 00:03:50.240
C of course stands for Creativity and is core
to the course, so in the first year creative

00:03:50.240 --> 00:03:56.300
design concepts are studied to build that
vital confidence in visual communication.

00:03:56.300 --> 00:04:01.450
Modules such as Motion Graphics and Compositing
as well as Interaction studied in the second

00:04:01.450 --> 00:04:06.180
year to develop advanced skills to help you
gain those vital first steps in industry and

00:04:06.180 --> 00:04:13.310
in the third year an individual project is
developed to allow you to create a portfolio

00:04:13.310 --> 00:04:17.070
piece ready to show to future employers.

00:04:17.070 --> 00:04:22.710
H stands for Holistic in the sense that creative
technology aims to develop a well-rounded

00:04:22.710 --> 00:04:29.530
student with skills to adapt and grab those
opportunities, not just in the present but

00:04:29.530 --> 00:04:33.060
also for the future.

00:04:33.060 --> 00:04:38.789
So please do visit the additional links provided
on this page and take a look at what our students

00:04:38.789 --> 00:04:44.430
have to say, the case histories as well as
student projects and if you have any questions,

00:04:44.430 --> 00:04:45.620
please do contact our administrators or myself.

